401 
402 protected:

404  IteratorType endIter;

406  virtual int_type underflow();
407 
408  virtual int_type uflow();

420  }

1460 template<typename TCharactersWriter>
1461 inline void Inspector<TCharactersWriter>::SetError(ErrorCode errorCode)
1462 {
1463  err = errorCode;
1464  if (errorCode != ErrorCode::None) {
1465  switch (errorCode) {
1466  case ErrorCode::StreamError:
1467  errMsg = "Stream error has occurred.";
1468  return;
1469  case ErrorCode::InvalidByteSequence:
1470  errMsg = "Invalid byte sequence.";
1471  return;
1472  case ErrorCode::UnknownEncoding:
1473  errMsg = "Unknown encoding.";
1474  return;
1475  case ErrorCode::EncodingConfusion:
1476  errMsg = "Encoding confusion.";
1477  return;
1478  case ErrorCode::EncodingDeclarationRequired:
1479  errMsg = "Encoding declaration must precede content that is not "
1480  "a legal UTF-8 or UTF-16.";
1481  return;
1482  case ErrorCode::InvalidSyntax:
1483  errMsg = "Invalid syntax.";
1484  return;
1485  case ErrorCode::InvalidXmlDeclarationLocation:
1486  errMsg = "Invalid location of XML declaration.";
1487  return;
1488  case ErrorCode::CDataSectionOutside:
1489  errMsg = "CDATA section is outside a root element.";
1490  return;
1491  case ErrorCode::ElementOutside:
1492  errMsg = "Element is outside a root element.";
1493  return;
1494  case ErrorCode::InvalidDocumentTypeDeclarationLocation:
1495  errMsg = "Invalid location of document type declaration.";
1496  return;
1497  case ErrorCode::DoubleDocumentTypeDeclaration:
1498  errMsg = "There should be exactly one document type declaration.";
1499  return;
1500  case ErrorCode::InvalidTagName:
1501  errMsg = "Invalid tag name.";
1502  return;
1503  case ErrorCode::InvalidAttributeName:
1504  errMsg = "Invalid attribute name.";
1505  return;
1506  case ErrorCode::UnclosedToken:
1507  errMsg = "Unclosed token.";
1508  return;
1509  case ErrorCode::InvalidReferenceSyntax:
1510  errMsg = "Invalid syntax of reference.";
1511  return;
1512  case ErrorCode::InvalidCharacterReference:
1513  errMsg = "Code point in character reference doesn\'t match "
1514  "the valid character in ISO/IEC 10646 character set.";
1515  return;
1516  case ErrorCode::UnexpectedEndTag:
1517  errMsg = "Unexpected end tag.";
1518  return;
1519  case ErrorCode::UnclosedTag:
1520  errMsg = "Unclosed tag.";
1521  return;
1522  case ErrorCode::NoElement:
1523  errMsg = "Cannot find an element.";
1524  return;
1525  case ErrorCode::DoubleAttributeName:
1526  errMsg = "An attribute name must not appear more than "
1527  "once in the same start-tag or empty-element tag.";
1528  return;
1529  case ErrorCode::PrefixWithoutAssignedNamespace:
1530  errMsg = "Name prefix must bound to the namespace URI.";
1531  return;
1532  case ErrorCode::PrefixWithEmptyNamespace:
1533  errMsg = "Namespace declaration with prefix cannot have an empty value.";
1534  return;
1535  case ErrorCode::XmlnsDeclared:
1536  errMsg = "Reserved xmlns prefix cannot be declared or set to an empty value.";
1537  return;
1538  case ErrorCode::PrefixBoundToReservedNamespace:
1539  errMsg = "Prefix is bound to reserved namespace.";
1540  return;
1541  case ErrorCode::ReservedNamespaceAsDefault:
1542  errMsg = "Reserved namespace cannot be declared as a default namespace.";
1543  return;
1544  case ErrorCode::InvalidXmlPrefixDeclaration:
1545  errMsg = "Prefix \'xml\' is reserved for use by XML and has a fixed "
1546  "namespace URI http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace.";
1547  return;
1548  default:
1549  errMsg = "XML error has occurred.";
1550  return;
1551  }
1552  }
1553  errMsg = nullptr;
1554 }

1556 template<typename TCharactersWriter>
1557 inline void Inspector<TCharactersWriter>::ParseBom()
1558 {
1559  if (sourceType == SourcePath) {
1560  fileStream.open(fPath.c_str(), std::ifstream::binary);
1561  if (!fileStream.is_open()) {
1562  fileStream.clear();
1563  SetError(ErrorCode::StreamError);
1564  return;
1565  }
1566 
1567  Details::Bom tempBom = Details::ReadBom(&fileStream);
1568  if (tempBom == Details::Bom::None || tempBom == Details::Bom::Utf8) {
1569  try {
1570  reader = new Encoding::Utf8StreamReader(&fileStream);
1571  } catch (...) {
1572  fileStream.close();
1573  fileStream.clear();
1574  throw;
1575  }
1576  err = ErrorCode::None;
1577  afterBom = true;
1578  bom = tempBom;
1579  eof = ((fileStream.rdstate() & std::istream::eofbit) != 0);
1580  return;
1581  }
1582 
1583  if (tempBom == Details::Bom::StreamError) {
1584  fileStream.close();
1585  fileStream.clear();
1586  SetError(ErrorCode::StreamError);
1587  return;
1588  }
1589 
1590  if (tempBom == Details::Bom::Invalid) {
1591  fileStream.close();
1592  fileStream.clear();
1593  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidByteSequence);
1594  eof = ((fileStream.rdstate() & std::istream::eofbit) != 0);
1595  return;
1596  }
1597 
1598  if (tempBom == Details::Bom::Utf16BE) {
1599  try {
1600  reader = new Encoding::Utf16BEStreamReader(&fileStream);
1601  } catch (...) {
1602  fileStream.close();
1603  fileStream.clear();
1604  throw;
1605  }
1606  err = ErrorCode::None;
1607  afterBom = true;
1608  bom = tempBom;
1609  } else if (tempBom == Details::Bom::Utf16LE) {
1610  try {
1611  reader = new Encoding::Utf16LEStreamReader(&fileStream);
1612  } catch (...) {
1613  fileStream.close();
1614  fileStream.clear();
1615  throw;
1616  }
1617  err = ErrorCode::None;
1618  afterBom = true;
1619  bom = tempBom;
1620  } else if (tempBom == Details::Bom::Utf32BE) {
1621  try {
1622  reader = new Encoding::Utf32BEStreamReader(&fileStream);
1623  } catch (...) {
1624  fileStream.close();
1625  fileStream.clear();
1626  throw;
1627  }
1628  err = ErrorCode::None;
1629  afterBom = true;
1630  bom = tempBom;
1631  } else if (tempBom == Details::Bom::Utf32LE) {
1632  try {
1633  reader = new Encoding::Utf32LEStreamReader(&fileStream);
1634  } catch (...) {
1635  fileStream.close();
1636  fileStream.clear();
1637  throw;
1638  }
1639  err = ErrorCode::None;
1640  afterBom = true;
1641  bom = tempBom;
1642  }
1643  } else if (sourceType == SourceStream || sourceType == SourceIterators) {
1644  Details::Bom tempBom = Details::ReadBom(inputStreamPtr);
1645  if (tempBom == Details::Bom::None || tempBom == Details::Bom::Utf8) {
1646  reader = new Encoding::Utf8StreamReader(inputStreamPtr);
1647  err = ErrorCode::None;
1648  afterBom = true;
1649  bom = tempBom;
1650  eof = ((inputStreamPtr->rdstate() & std::istream::eofbit) != 0);
1651  return;
1652  }
1653 
1654  if (tempBom == Details::Bom::StreamError) {
1655  SetError(ErrorCode::StreamError);
1656  return;
1657  }
1658 
1659  if (tempBom == Details::Bom::Invalid) {
1660  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidByteSequence);
1661  eof = ((inputStreamPtr->rdstate() & std::istream::eofbit) != 0);
1662  return;
1663  }
1664 
1665  if (tempBom == Details::Bom::Utf16BE) {
1666  reader = new Encoding::Utf16BEStreamReader(inputStreamPtr);
1667  err = ErrorCode::None;
1668  afterBom = true;
1669  bom = tempBom;
1670  } else if (tempBom == Details::Bom::Utf16LE) {
1671  reader = new Encoding::Utf16LEStreamReader(inputStreamPtr);
1672  err = ErrorCode::None;
1673  afterBom = true;
1674  bom = tempBom;
1675  } else if (tempBom == Details::Bom::Utf32BE) {
1676  reader = new Encoding::Utf32BEStreamReader(inputStreamPtr);
1677  err = ErrorCode::None;
1678  afterBom = true;
1679  bom = tempBom;
1680  } else if (tempBom == Details::Bom::Utf32LE) {
1681  reader = new Encoding::Utf32LEStreamReader(inputStreamPtr);
1682  err = ErrorCode::None;
1683  afterBom = true;
1684  bom = tempBom;
1685  }
1686  } else if (sourceType == SourceReader) {
1687  err = ErrorCode::None;
1688  afterBom = true;
1689  } else {
1690  SetError(ErrorCode::StreamError);
1691  }
1692 }
1693 
1694 template<typename TCharactersWriter>
1695 inline bool Inspector<TCharactersWriter>::ParseElement()
1696 {
1697  // currentCharacter == name start character.
1698  // and
1699  // currentCharacter != Colon.
1700  SizeType tempRow = currentRow;
1701  SizeType tempColumn = currentColumn;
1702 
1703  if (unclosedTagsSize == 0 && foundElement) {
1704  tempRow = row;
1705  tempColumn = column;
1706  Reset();
1707  SetError(ErrorCode::ElementOutside);
1708  row = tempRow;
1709  column = tempColumn;
1710  return false;
1711  }
1712 
1713  PrepareNode();
1714 
1715  // Element name.
1716  do {
1717  CharactersWriterType::WriteCharacter(name, currentCharacter);
1718  CharactersWriterType::WriteCharacter(localName, currentCharacter);
1719 
1720  if (NextCharBad(true)) {
1721  return false;
1722  }
1723 
1724  if (currentCharacter == Colon) {
1725  // Prefixed name.
1726  prefix = name;
1727  localName.clear();
1728  CharactersWriterType::WriteCharacter(name, currentCharacter);
1729 
1730  if (NextCharBad(true)) {
1731  return false;
1732  }
1733 
1734  if (currentCharacter == Colon ||
1735  !Encoding::CharactersReader::IsNameStartChar(currentCharacter))
1736  {
1737  Reset();
1738  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidTagName);
1739  row = tempRow;
1740  column = tempColumn;
1741  return false;
1742  }
1743 
1744  do {
1745  CharactersWriterType::WriteCharacter(name, currentCharacter);
1746  CharactersWriterType::WriteCharacter(localName, currentCharacter);
1747 
1748  if (NextCharBad(true)) {
1749  return false;
1750  }
1751 
1752  if (currentCharacter == Colon) {
1753  Reset();
1754  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidTagName);
1755  row = tempRow;
1756  column = tempColumn;
1757  return false;
1758  }
1759  } while (Encoding::CharactersReader::IsNameChar(currentCharacter));
1760  break;
1761  }
1762  } while (Encoding::CharactersReader::IsNameChar(currentCharacter));
1763 
1764  if (currentCharacter == GreaterThan) {
1765  node = Inspected::StartTag;
1766  bool noErrors = NamespacesStuff();
1767  if (noErrors) {
1768  UnclosedTagType & ref = NewUnclosedTag();
1769  ref.Name = name;
1770  ref.LocalName = localName;
1771  ref.Prefix = prefix;
1772  ref.NamespaceUri = namespaceUri;
1773  ref.Row = row;
1774  ref.Column = column;
1775  foundElement = true;
1776  return true;
1777  }
1778  return false;
1779  }
1780 
1781  if (currentCharacter == Slash) {
1782  // <tagName/
1783  if (NextCharBad(true)) {
1784  return false;
1785  }
1786  if (currentCharacter != GreaterThan) {
1787  tempRow = currentRow;
1788  tempColumn = currentColumn;
1789  Reset();
1790  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidSyntax);
1791  row = tempRow;
1792  column = tempColumn;
1793  return false;
1794  }
1795 
1796  node = Inspected::EmptyElementTag;
1797  bool noErrors = NamespacesStuff();
1798  if (noErrors) {
1799  foundElement = true;
1800  return true;
1801  }
1802  return false;
1803  }
1804 
1805  if (IsWhiteSpace(currentCharacter)) {
1806  // Ignore white spaces.
1807  do {
1808  if (NextCharBad(true)) {
1809  return false;
1810  }
1811  } while (IsWhiteSpace(currentCharacter));
1812 
1813  if (currentCharacter != Colon &&
1814  Encoding::CharactersReader::IsNameStartChar(currentCharacter))
1815  {
1816  // Attributes.
1817  return ParseAttributes();
1818  }
1819 
1820  if (currentCharacter == Slash) {
1821  // <tagName /
1822  if (NextCharBad(true)) {
1823  return false;
1824  }
1825  if (currentCharacter != GreaterThan) {
1826  tempRow = currentRow;
1827  tempColumn = currentColumn;
1828  Reset();
1829  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidSyntax);
1830  row = tempRow;
1831  column = tempColumn;
1832  return false;
1833  }
1834 
1835  node = Inspected::EmptyElementTag;
1836  bool noErrors = NamespacesStuff();
1837  if (noErrors) {
1838  foundElement = true;
1839  return true;
1840  }
1841  return false;
1842  }
1843 
1844  if (currentCharacter == GreaterThan) {
1845  // <tagName >
1846  node = Inspected::StartTag;
1847  bool noErrors = NamespacesStuff();
1848  if (noErrors) {
1849  UnclosedTagType & ref = NewUnclosedTag();
1850  ref.Name = name;
1851  ref.LocalName = localName;
1852  ref.Prefix = prefix;
1853  ref.NamespaceUri = namespaceUri;
1854  ref.Row = row;
1855  ref.Column = column;
1856  foundElement = true;
1857  return true;
1858  }
1859  return false;
1860  }
1861 
1862  if (Encoding::CharactersReader::IsNameChar(currentCharacter)) {
1863  // For example <tagName 123attr="value">
1864  // 1 is not allowed as a first character name.
1865  tempRow = currentRow;
1866  tempColumn = currentColumn;
1867  Reset();
1868  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidAttributeName);
1869  row = tempRow;
1870  column = tempColumn;
1871  return false;
1872  }
1873 
1874  // Invalid syntax.
1875  // For example <tagName !abc...
1876  // ! is not allowed as a part of the name.
1877  tempRow = currentRow;
1878  tempColumn = currentColumn;
1879  Reset();
1880  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidSyntax);
1881  row = tempRow;
1882  column = tempColumn;
1883  return false;
1884  }
1885 
1886  // Invalid tag name.
1887  Reset();
1888  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidTagName);
1889  row = tempRow;
1890  column = tempColumn;
1891  return false;
1892 }
1893 
1894 
1895 template<typename TCharactersWriter>
1896 inline bool Inspector<TCharactersWriter>::ParseAttributes()
1897 {
1898  // IsNameStartChar(currentCharacter) == true
1899  // and
1900  // currentCharacter != Colon
1901 
1902  SizeType tempRow;
1903  SizeType tempColumn;
1904  bool white = true;
1905 
1906  do { // {...} while (Encoding::CharactersReader::IsNameStartChar(currentCharacter));
1907  AttributeType & attr = NewAttribute();
1908  attr.Row = currentRow;
1909  attr.Column = currentColumn;
1910 
1911  // attribute.Name, attribute.LocalName, attribute.Prefix.
1912  do { // {...} while (Encoding::CharactersReader::IsNameChar(currentCharacter));
1913  CharactersWriterType::WriteCharacter(attr.Name, currentCharacter);
1914  CharactersWriterType::WriteCharacter(attr.LocalName, currentCharacter);
1915 
1916  if (NextCharBad(true)) {
1917  return false;
1918  }
1919 
1920  if (currentCharacter == Colon) {
1921  // Prefixed name.
1922  attr.Prefix = attr.Name;
1923  attr.LocalName.clear();
1924  CharactersWriterType::WriteCharacter(attr.Name, currentCharacter);
1925 
1926  if (NextCharBad(true)) {
1927  return false;
1928  }
1929 
1930  if (currentCharacter == Colon ||
1931  !Encoding::CharactersReader::IsNameStartChar(currentCharacter))
1932  {
1933  Reset();
1934  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidAttributeName);
1935  row = attr.Row;
1936  column = attr.Column;
1937  return false;

3722 template<typename TCharactersWriter>
3723 inline bool Inspector<TCharactersWriter>::NamespacesStuff()
3724 {
3725  // Collect namespaces from attributes.
3726  typedef typename std::deque<AttributeType>::iterator AttrIter;
3727  AttrIter attrEnd = attributes.begin() + attributesSize;
3728  for (AttrIter attr = attributes.begin(); attr != attrEnd; ++attr) {
3729  if (attr->Prefix.empty()) {
3730  if (attr->LocalName == xmlnsString) {
3731  // Default namespace.
3732  // <mytag xmlns=...
3733  if (attr->Value == xmlUriString ||
3734  attr->Value == xmlnsUriString)
3735  {
3736  // <mytag xmlns="http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace"...
3737  // or
3738  // <mytag xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/xmlns/"...
3739  Reset();
3740  SetError(ErrorCode::ReservedNamespaceAsDefault);
3741  row = attr->Row;
3742  column = attr->Column;
3743  return false;
3744  }
3745 
3746  NamespaceDeclarationType & ref = NewNamespace();
3747  ref.Uri = attr->Value;
3748  ref.TagIndex = static_cast<SizeType>(unclosedTagsSize);
3749  }
3750  } else if (attr->Prefix == xmlnsString) {
3751  if (attr->LocalName == xmlnsString) {
3752  // <mytag xmlns:xmlns=...
3753  Reset();
3754  SetError(ErrorCode::XmlnsDeclared);
3755  row = attr->Row;
3756  column = attr->Column;
3757  return false;
3758  } else if (attr->LocalName == lowerXmlString) {
3759  // <mytag xmlns:xml=...
3760 
3761  if (attr->Value != xmlUriString) {
3762  Reset();
3763  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidXmlPrefixDeclaration);
3764  row = attr->Row;
3765  column = attr->Column;
3766  return false;
3767  }
3768  } else if (attr->Value == xmlUriString || attr->Value == xmlnsUriString) {
3769  // <mytag xmlns:newprefix="http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace"...
3770  // or
3771  // <mytag xmlns:newprefix="http://www.w3.org/2000/xmlns/"...
3772  Reset();
3773  SetError(ErrorCode::PrefixBoundToReservedNamespace);
3774  row = attr->Row;
3775  column = attr->Column;
3776  return false;
3777  } else if (attr->Value.empty()) {
3778  // <mytag xmlns:newprefix=""...
3779  Reset();
3780  SetError(ErrorCode::PrefixWithEmptyNamespace);
3781  row = attr->Row;
3782  column = attr->Column;
3783  return false;
3784  } else {
3785  NamespaceDeclarationType & ref = NewNamespace();
3786  ref.Prefix = attr->LocalName;
3787  ref.Uri = attr->Value;
3788  ref.TagIndex = static_cast<SizeType>(unclosedTagsSize);
3789  }
3790  }
3791  }
3792 
3793  // Assign URIs to attributes.
3794  typedef typename std::deque<NamespaceDeclarationType>::const_iterator NamespaceIter;
3795  NamespaceIter namespaceLast = namespaces.begin();
3796  if (namespacesSize != 0) {
3797  namespaceLast += (namespacesSize - 1);
3798  }
3799  for (AttrIter attr = attributes.begin(); attr != attrEnd; ++attr) {
3800  if (!attr->Prefix.empty()) {
3801  if (attr->Prefix == xmlnsString) {
3802  attr->NamespaceUri = xmlnsUriString;
3803  } else if (attr->Prefix == lowerXmlString) {
3804  attr->NamespaceUri = xmlUriString;
3805  } else {
3806  bool found = false;
3807  NamespaceIter n = namespaceLast;
3808  for ( ; n != namespaces.begin(); --n) {
3809  if (attr->Prefix == n->Prefix) {
3810  found = true;
3811  break;
3812  }
3813  }
3814  if (!found && (namespacesSize == 0 || attr->Prefix != n->Prefix)) {
3815  Reset();
3816  SetError(ErrorCode::PrefixWithoutAssignedNamespace);
3817  row = attr->Row;
3818  column = attr->Column;
3819  return false;
3820  } else {
3821  attr->NamespaceUri = n->Uri;
3822  }
3823  }
3824  }
3825  }
3826 
3827  // Assign URI to element.
3828  if (!prefix.empty()) {
3829  if (prefix == xmlnsString) {
3830  // row and column => '<'
3831  SizeType tempRow = row;
3832  SizeType tempColumn = column + 1;
3833  Reset();
3834  SetError(ErrorCode::PrefixWithoutAssignedNamespace);
3835  row = tempRow;
3836  column = tempColumn;
3837  return false;
3838  } else if (prefix == lowerXmlString) {
3839  namespaceUri = xmlUriString;
3840  } else {
3841  bool found = false;
3842  NamespaceIter n = namespaceLast;
3843  for ( ; n != namespaces.begin(); --n) {
3844  if (prefix == n->Prefix) {
3845  found = true;
3846  break;
3847  }
3848  }
3849  if (!found && (namespacesSize == 0 || prefix != n->Prefix)) {
3850  // row and column => '<'
3851  SizeType tempRow = row;
3852  SizeType tempColumn = column + 1;
3853  Reset();
3854  SetError(ErrorCode::PrefixWithoutAssignedNamespace);
3855  row = tempRow;
3856  column = tempColumn;
3857  return false;
3858  } else {
3859  namespaceUri = n->Uri;
3860  }
3861  }
3862  } else { // prefix.empty() == true.
3863  // Find default namespace.
3864  bool found = false;
3865  NamespaceIter n = namespaceLast;
3866  for ( ; n != namespaces.begin(); --n) {
3867  if (n->Prefix.empty()) {
3868  found = true;
3869  break;
3870  }
3871  }
3872  if (found || (namespacesSize != 0 && n->Prefix.empty())) {
3873  namespaceUri = n->Uri;
3874  }
3875  }
3876 
3877  // Ensure no double attribute name like:
3878  // <a x:local="first" y:local="second">
3879  // where x and y prefixes are bound to the same namespace URI.
3880  if (attributesSize > 1) {
3881  AttrIter attrEndMinus1 = attributes.begin() + (attributesSize - 1);
3882  for (AttrIter attr = attributes.begin(); attr != attrEndMinus1; ++attr) {
3883  if (!attr->Prefix.empty()) {
3884  for (AttrIter next = attr + 1; next != attrEnd; ++next) {
3885  if (attr->LocalName == next->LocalName &&
3886  attr->NamespaceUri == next->NamespaceUri)
3887  {
3888  Reset();
3889  SetError(ErrorCode::DoubleAttributeName);
3890  row = next->Row;
3891  column = next->Column;
3892  return false;
3893  }
3894  }
3895  }
3896  }
3897  }
3898 
3899  return true;
3900 }

3903 inline bool Inspector<TCharactersWriter>::ParseCharacterReference(char32_t & result, bool insideTag)
3904 {

3906

3926  int radix = 10;
3927

3930  radix = 16;

3945 
3946  // Ignore leading zeros.

3965  buffer[digitCount++] = static_cast<unsigned char>(digit);
3966  if (NextCharBad(insideTag)) {
3967  if (!insideTag && eof) {
3968  UnclosedTagType & ref = unclosedTags[unclosedTagsSize - 1];
3969  Reset();
3970  SetError(ErrorCode::UnclosedTag);

3973  eof = true;
3974  }

3976  }

3978  }

3984  if (digitCount == 0) {
3985  if (leadingZeros) {
3986  Reset();
3987  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidCharacterReference);
3988  row = tempRow;
3989  column = tempColumn;
3990  } else {
3991  Reset();
3992  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidReferenceSyntax);
3993  row = tempRow;
3994  column = tempColumn;
3995  }
3996  return false;
3997  }
3998 
3999  // We are sure that digitCount is 7 max.
4000  result = 0;
4001  for (int i = 0; i < digitCount; ++i) {
4002  result = result * radix + static_cast<char32_t>(buffer[i]);
4003  }
4004 
4005  if (!Encoding::CharactersReader::IsChar(result)) {
4006  Reset();
4007  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidCharacterReference);
4008  row = tempRow;
4009  column = tempColumn;
4010  return false;
4011  }
4012  } else if (digit >= 0 && digit < radix) {
4013  // To many digits, but we must check the syntax to set appropriate error.
4014 
4015  do {
4016  if (NextCharBad(insideTag)) {
4017  if (!insideTag && eof) {
4018  UnclosedTagType & ref = unclosedTags[unclosedTagsSize - 1];
4019  Reset();
4020  SetError(ErrorCode::UnclosedTag);
4021  row = ref.Row;
4022  column = ref.Column;
4023  eof = true;
4024  }
4025  return false;
4026  }
4027  digit = Encoding::CharactersReader::GetHexDigitValue(currentCharacter);
4028  } while (digit >= 0 && digit < radix);
4029 
4030  if (currentCharacter == Semicolon) {
4031  // just invalid code point.
4032  Reset();
4033  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidCharacterReference);
4034  row = tempRow;
4035  column = tempColumn;
4036  } else {
4037  // Invalid syntax of character reference, not just invalid code point.
4038  Reset();
4039  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidReferenceSyntax);
4040  row = tempRow;
4041  column = tempColumn;
4042  }
4043  return false;
4044  } else {
4045  // Not allowed character.
4046  Reset();
4047  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidReferenceSyntax);
4048  row = tempRow;
4049  column = tempColumn;
4050  return false;
4051  }

4262  if (NextCharBad(insideTag)) {
4263  if (!insideTag && eof) {
4264  UnclosedTagType & ref = unclosedTags[unclosedTagsSize - 1];
4265  Reset();
4266  SetError(ErrorCode::UnclosedTag);
4267  row = ref.Row;
4268  column = ref.Column;
4269  eof = true;
4270  }
4271  return -1;
4272  }
4273 
4274  if (currentCharacter == Semicolon) {
4275  // "&apos;"
4276  currentCharacter = SingleQuote;
4277  entityName.clear();
4278  return 1;
4279  }
4280  }
4281  }
4282  }
4283 
4284  if (currentCharacter == Semicolon) {
4285  return 0;
4286  } else if (!Encoding::CharactersReader::IsNameChar(currentCharacter) || // NOLINT
4287  currentCharacter == Colon)
4288  {
4289  Reset();
4290  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidReferenceSyntax);
4291  row = tempRow;
4292  column = tempColumn;
4293  return -1;
4294  }
4295  } else if (currentCharacter == QuotEntityName[0]) {
4296  // "&q"
4297  CharactersWriterType::WriteCharacter(entityName, currentCharacter);
4298  ++entityNameCharCount;
4299  std::size_t i;
4300  for (i = 1; i < 4; ++i) {
4301  if (NextCharBad(insideTag)) {
4302  if (!insideTag && eof) {
4303  UnclosedTagType & ref = unclosedTags[unclosedTagsSize - 1];
4304  Reset();
4305  SetError(ErrorCode::UnclosedTag);
4306  row = ref.Row;
4307  column = ref.Column;
4308  eof = true;
4309  }
4310  return -1;
4311  }
4312 
4313  if (currentCharacter != QuotEntityName[i]) {
4314  break;
4315  }
4316 
4317  CharactersWriterType::WriteCharacter(entityName, currentCharacter);
4318  ++entityNameCharCount;
4319  }
4320 
4321  if (i == 4) {
4322  if (NextCharBad(insideTag)) {
4323  if (!insideTag && eof) {
4324  UnclosedTagType & ref = unclosedTags[unclosedTagsSize - 1];
4325  Reset();
4326  SetError(ErrorCode::UnclosedTag);
4327  row = ref.Row;
4328  column = ref.Column;
4329  eof = true;
4330  }
4331  return -1;
4332  }
4333  }
4334 
4335  if (currentCharacter == Semicolon) {
4336  if (i == 4) {
4337  // "&quot;"
4338  currentCharacter = DoubleQuote;
4339  entityName.clear();
4340  return 1;
4341  } else {
4342  return 0;
4343  }
4344  } else if (!Encoding::CharactersReader::IsNameChar(currentCharacter) || // NOLINT
4345  currentCharacter == Colon) // NOLINT
4346  { // NOLINT
4347  Reset();
4348  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidReferenceSyntax);
4349  row = tempRow;
4350  column = tempColumn;
4351  return -1;
4352  }
4353  }
4354 
4355  do {
4356  CharactersWriterType::WriteCharacter(entityName, currentCharacter);
4357  ++entityNameCharCount;
4358  if (NextCharBad(insideTag)) {
4359  if (!insideTag && eof) {
4360  UnclosedTagType & ref = unclosedTags[unclosedTagsSize - 1];
4361  Reset();
4362  SetError(ErrorCode::UnclosedTag);
4363  row = ref.Row;
4364  column = ref.Column;
4365  eof = true;
4366  }
4367  return -1;
4368  }
4369 
4370  if (currentCharacter == Colon) {
4371  Reset();
4372  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidReferenceSyntax);
4373  row = tempRow;
4374  column = tempColumn;
4375  return -1;
4376  }
4377  } while (Encoding::CharactersReader::IsNameChar(currentCharacter));
4378 
4379  if (currentCharacter != Semicolon) {
4380  Reset();
4381  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidReferenceSyntax);
4382  row = tempRow;
4383  column = tempColumn;
4384  return -1;
4385  }
4386 
4387  return 0;
4388 }

4392 {
4393  if (attributesSize > 1) {

4395  const AttributeType & last = attributes[lastIndex];
4396  for (AttributesSizeType i = 0; i < lastIndex; ++i) {
4397  if (last.Name == attributes[i].Name) {
4398  Reset();
4399  SetError(ErrorCode::DoubleAttributeName);
4400  row = last.Row;
4401  column = last.Column;
4402  return false;
4403  }
4404  }
4405  }
4406 
4407  return true;

5751 
5752  return true;

5813 template<typename TCharactersWriter>
5814 inline bool Inspector<TCharactersWriter>::NextCharBad(bool insideTag)
5815 {
5816  // x, CR, LF, y => x, LF, y
5817  // x, CR, y => x, LF, y
5818  // x, LF, CR, y => x, LF, LF, y
5819  // Check http://www.w3.org/TR/2008/REC-xml-20081126/#sec-line-ends.
5820 
5821  SizeType tempRow;
5822  SizeType tempColumn;
5823 
5824  if (currentCharacter == LineFeed) {
5825  ++currentRow;
5826  currentColumn = 1;
5827  } else {
5828  ++currentColumn;
5829  }
5830 
5831  if (bufferedCharacter != 0) {
5832  if (bufferedCharacter > 3) { // Allowed character.
5833  currentCharacter = bufferedCharacter;
5834  bufferedCharacter = 0;
5835  return false;
5836  }
5837 
5838  if (bufferedCharacter == 1) { // No more characters to read.
5839  if (insideTag) {
5840  // Start token position.
5841  tempRow = row;
5842  tempColumn = column;
5843  Reset();
5844  row = tempRow;
5845  column = tempColumn;
5846  SetError(ErrorCode::UnclosedToken);
5847  eof = true;
5848  } else {
5849  eof = true;
5850  bufferedCharacter = 0;
5851  }
5852  } else if (bufferedCharacter == 2) { // Character is not allowed in XML document.
5853  // Invalid character position.
5854  tempRow = currentRow;
5855  tempColumn = currentColumn;
5856  Reset();
5857  row = tempRow;
5858  column = tempColumn;
5859  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidByteSequence);
5860  } else { // bufferedCharacter == 3 // Stream error.
5861  // Character at stream error position.
5862  tempRow = currentRow;
5863  tempColumn = currentColumn;
5864  Reset();
5865  row = tempRow;
5866  column = tempColumn;
5867  SetError(ErrorCode::StreamError);
5868  }
5869  afterBom = true;
5870  return true;
5871  }
5872 
5873  int result = reader->ReadCharacter(currentCharacter);
5874 
5875  if (result == 1) { // Character was read successfully.
5876  if (currentCharacter == CarriageReturn) { // We don't like CR.
5877  result = reader->ReadCharacter(currentCharacter);
5878  if (result == 1) { // Second character was read successfully.
5879  if (currentCharacter != LineFeed) {
5880  // CR, x => LF, x
5881  bufferedCharacter = currentCharacter;
5882  currentCharacter = LineFeed;
5883  }
5884  // else CR, LF => LF
5885  } else if (result == 0) { // No more characters to read.
5886  // CR, [end of document] => LF, [end of document]
5887  bufferedCharacter = 1;
5888  currentCharacter = LineFeed;
5889  } else if (result == -1) { // Character is not allowed in XML document.
5890  // CR, [not allowed character] => LF, [not allowed character]
5891  bufferedCharacter = 2;
5892  currentCharacter = LineFeed;
5893  } else { // result == -2 // Stream error.
5894  // CR, [stream error] => LF, [stream error]
5895  bufferedCharacter = 3;
5896  currentCharacter = LineFeed;
5897  }
5898  }
5899  return false;
5900  }
5901 
5902  if (result == 0) { // No more characters to read.
5903  if (insideTag) {
5904  // Start token position.
5905  tempRow = row;
5906  tempColumn = column;
5907  Reset();
5908  row = tempRow;
5909  column = tempColumn;
5910  SetError(ErrorCode::UnclosedToken);
5911  eof = true;
5912  } else {
5913  eof = true;
5914  }
5915  } else if (result == -1) { // Character is not allowed in XML document.
5916  // Invalid character position.
5917  tempRow = currentRow;
5918  tempColumn = currentColumn;
5919  Reset();
5920  row = tempRow;
5921  column = tempColumn;
5922  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidByteSequence);
5923  } else { // result == -2 // Stream error.
5924  // Character at stream error position.
5925  tempRow = currentRow;
5926  tempColumn = currentColumn;
5927  Reset();
5928  row = tempRow;
5929  column = tempColumn;
5930  SetError(ErrorCode::StreamError);
5931  }
5932  afterBom = true;
5933  return true;
5934 }

5936 template<typename TCharactersWriter>
5937 inline bool Inspector<TCharactersWriter>::Inspect()
5938 {
5939  SizeType tempRow;
5940  SizeType tempColumn;
5941  if (!afterBom && (err == ErrorCode::None || err == ErrorCode::StreamError)) {
5942  // First call of Inspect method or after stream error while BOM parsing.
5943  ParseBom();
5944  if (err != ErrorCode::None) {
5945  return false;
5946  }
5947  row = 1;
5948  column = 1;
5949  if (eof) {
5950  SetError(ErrorCode::NoElement);
5951  return false;
5952  }
5953  currentRow = 1;
5954  currentColumn = 0; // Don't worry,
5955  // it will be 1 after first call of NextCharBad method.
5956 
5957  // First character.
5958  if (NextCharBad(false)) {
5959  if (eof) {
5960  SetError(ErrorCode::NoElement);
5961  return false;
5962  }
5963  }
5964 
5965  if (sourceType != SourceReader &&
5966  bom != Details::Bom::None &&

5968  bom != Details::Bom::Utf16BE &&

5972

5974  Reset();
5975  SetError(ErrorCode::EncodingDeclarationRequired);

5977  column = 1;
5978  return false;
5979  }
5980 
5981  if (NextCharBad(true)) {
5982  return false;
5983  }
5984 
5985  if (currentCharacter != Question) {
5986  Reset();
5987  SetError(ErrorCode::EncodingDeclarationRequired);
5988  row = 1;
5989  column = 1;
5990  return false;
5991  }
5992

5994  if (NextCharBad(true)) {
5995  return false;
5996  }
5997  if (currentCharacter != LowerXml[i]) {
5998  Reset();
5999  SetError(ErrorCode::EncodingDeclarationRequired);
6000  row = 1;
6001  column = 1;
6002  return false;
6003  }
6004  CharactersWriterType::WriteCharacter(name, currentCharacter);
6005  CharactersWriterType::WriteCharacter(localName, currentCharacter);
6006  }
6007 
6008  // '<?xml'
6009  if (NextCharBad(true)) {
6010  return false;
6011  }
6012 
6013  if (!IsWhiteSpace(currentCharacter)) {
6014  Reset();
6015  SetError(ErrorCode::EncodingDeclarationRequired);
6016  row = 1;
6017  column = 1;
6018  return false;
6019  }
6020 
6021  return ParseXmlDeclaration();
6022  }
6023 
6024  if (IsWhiteSpace(currentCharacter)) {
6025  do {
6026  CharactersWriterType::WriteCharacter(value, currentCharacter);
6027  if (NextCharBad(false)) {
6028  if (eof) { // White spaces followed by end of file.
6029  // In XML document at least one root element is required.
6030  tempRow = currentRow;
6031  tempColumn = currentColumn;
6032  Reset();
6033  SetError(ErrorCode::NoElement);
6034  row = tempRow;
6035  column = tempColumn;
6036  return false;
6037  } else { // White spaces followed by invalid character or stream error.
6038  // Error is set already.
6039  return false;
6040  }
6041  }
6042  } while (IsWhiteSpace(currentCharacter));
6043 
6044  if (currentCharacter != LessThan) {
6045  tempRow = currentRow;
6046  tempColumn = currentColumn;
6047  Reset();
6048  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidSyntax);
6049  row = tempRow;
6050  column = tempColumn;
6051  return false;
6052  }
6053 
6054  node = Inspected::Whitespace;
6055  return true;
6056  }
6057 
6058  if (currentCharacter != LessThan) {
6059  tempRow = currentRow;
6060  tempColumn = currentColumn;
6061  Reset();
6062  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidSyntax);
6063  row = tempRow;
6064  column = tempColumn;
6065  }
6066  }
6067 
6068  if (err != ErrorCode::None) {
6069  return false;
6070  }
6071 
6072  if (currentCharacter == GreaterThan) {
6073  // End of token.
6074  if (NextCharBad(false) && !eof) {
6075  return false;
6076  }
6077  } else if (currentCharacter == Semicolon) {
6078  if (!entityName.empty()) {

6080  name = entityName;
6081  localName = entityName;
6082  entityName.clear();

6084  row = currentRow;
6085  column = (currentColumn - entityNameCharCount - 1);
6086  return true;
6087  } else {
6088  // End of reference.
6089  if (NextCharBad(false) && !eof) {
6090  return false;
6091  }
6092  }
6093  }
6094 
6095  if (eof) {
6096  if (!foundElement) {
6097  // In XML document at least one root element is required.
6098  tempRow = currentRow;
6099  tempColumn = currentColumn;
6100  Reset();
6101  SetError(ErrorCode::NoElement);
6102  row = tempRow;
6103  column = tempColumn;
6104  } else if (unclosedTagsSize != 0) {
6105  UnclosedTagType & ref = unclosedTags[unclosedTagsSize - 1];
6106  Reset();
6107  SetError(ErrorCode::UnclosedTag);
6108  row = ref.Row;
6109  column = ref.Column;
6110  foundElement = true;
6111  } else {
6112  // XML document is fully parsed without any error.
6113  tempRow = currentRow;
6114  tempColumn = currentColumn;
6115  Reset();
6116  row = tempRow;
6117  column = tempColumn;
6118  currentRow = tempRow;
6119  currentColumn = tempColumn;
6120  foundElement = true;
6121  afterBom = true;
6122  }
6123  currentCharacter = 0;
6124  eof = true;
6125  return false;
6126  }
6127 
6128  if (currentCharacter == LessThan) { // New tag to parse.
6129  SavePosition();
6130 
6131  // Go to the next character after '<'.
6132  if (NextCharBad(true)) {
6133  return false;
6134  }
6135 
6136  if (currentCharacter == Slash) {
6137  // EndTag.
6138  return ParseEndTag();
6139  }
6140 
6141  if (currentCharacter != Colon &&
6142  Encoding::CharactersReader::IsNameStartChar(currentCharacter))
6143  {
6144  // StartTag or EmptyElementTag.
6145  return ParseElement();
6146  }
6147 
6148  if (currentCharacter == Exclamation) {
6149  // Comment or DocumentType.
6150  return ParseExclamation();
6151  }
6152 
6153  if (currentCharacter == Question) {
6154  // XmlDeclaration or ProcessingInstruction.
6155  return ParseQuestion();
6156  }
6157 
6158  // currentCharacter is not allowed here.
6159  tempRow = currentRow;
6160  tempColumn = currentColumn;
6161  if (Encoding::CharactersReader::IsNameChar(currentCharacter)) {
6162  // Not allowed as start character of the name,
6163  // but allowed as a part of this name.
6164  Reset();
6165  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidTagName);
6166  } else {
6167  // Some weird character.
6168  Reset();
6169  SetError(ErrorCode::InvalidSyntax);
6170  }
6171  row = tempRow;
6172  column = tempColumn;
6173  return false;
6174  }
6175 
6176  // currentCharacter == first character of text.
6177  SavePosition();
6178  return ParseText();
6179 }

6407  }
